to, sed faucibus ligula feugiat ac. Morbi quis enim nulla, vel congue augue.</span>Donec eget dignissim augue. Donec ante felis, aliquam ut consequat eget, lobortis dapibus risus. Aliquam laoreet enim et lectus ornare hendrerit. Aliquam rhoncus enim libero. Morbi aliquam, nibh mattis feugiat dapibus, nisi massa adipiscing justo, sit amet condimentum urna ipsum et lacus. Nam fermentum, eros quis ullamcorper convallis, libero mauris lacinia eros, sed tempus leo lorem vitae purus.</p>\r\n<br /> <br />\r\n<p><small>&lt;p&gt; Here goes main part of the text &lt;span class=\"gkBlockTextCenter\"&gt;Block of text&lt;/span&gt;rest of the text&lt;/p&gt; </small></p>\r\n<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum condimentum pulvinar justo, sed faucibus ligula feugiat ac. Morbi quis enim nulla, vel congue augue. Duis quis quam sed purus porta eleifend.<span class=\"gkBlockTextCenter\">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum condimentum pulvinar justo, sed faucibus ligula feugiat ac. Morbi quis enim nulla, vel congue augue.</span>Donec eget dignissim augue. Donec ante felis, aliquam ut consequat eget, lobortis dapibus risus. Aliquam laoreet enim et lectus ornare hendrerit. Aliquam rhoncus enim libero. Morbi aliquam, nibh mattis feugiat dapibus, nisi massa adipiscing justo, sit amet condimentum urna ipsum et lacus. Nam fermentum, eros quis ullamcorper convallis, libero mauris lacinia eros, sed tempus leo lorem vitae purus. Nunc a malesuada felis. Cras ultrices sapien eu nisi elementum non blandit urna sodales.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Additional typography elements</h3>\r\n<p>You can create social icons like the following icons by using simple code and anchor elements:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a class=\"gkFacebook\" href=\"#\">Facebook</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkTwitter\" href=\"#\">Twitter</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkVimeo\" href=\"#\">Vimeo</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkMoby\" href=\"#\">Moby</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkSkype\" href=\"#\">Skype</a>\r\n<a class=\"gkYoutube\" href=\"#\">YouTube</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkDigg\" href=\"#\">Digg</a> \r\n<a class=\"gkDropbox\" href=\"#\">Dropbox</a>  \r\n</p>\r\n<div class=\"clr\"> </div>\r\n<pre>&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkFacebook\"&gt;Facebook&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkTwitter\"&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkVimeo\"&gt;Vimeo&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkMoby\"&gt;Moby&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkSkype\"&gt;Skype&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkYoutube\"&gt;YouTube&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkDigg\"&gt;Digg&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=\"#\" class=\"gkDropbox\"&gt;Dropbox&lt;/a&gt;<br /></pre>\r\n<div class=\"clr\"> </div>\r\n<p>You can create small logo with using div containing class <strong>gkDemoLogo</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><div class=\"gkDemoLogo\">Demo logo</div></p>\r\n<p>To create a chalkboard with text inside please create a div with <strong>gkChalkboard</strong> class:</p>\r\n<p><div class=\"gkChalkboard\"><strong>Example</strong><p>Item number one</p><p>Item number two</p></div></p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;div class=\"gkChalkboard\"&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Item number one&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Item number two&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Simple animation engine</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For creating simple intro animations like the animation on the homepage we recommend to use our simple animation engine based on the data-* attributes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For creating animation please creata a container with class <strong>gkHeader</strong> and put elements inside it. We have prepared elements like: <strong>h1</strong>, <strong>p</strong>, <strong>p small</strong>, <strong>div.gkHeaderHat</strong>, <strong>div.gkHeaderOrder</strong>, <strong>div.gkHeaderSign</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All elements are hidden by opacity set to 0. You have to specify at least two attributes: <strong>data-start</strong> and <strong>data-end</strong>. The first attribute contains starting properties for the element and these properties should be written with units. The second attribute specify which properties will be animated and what will be their final value (without units).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are also two additional attributes: <strong>data-time</strong> and <strong>data-delay</strong>. The <strong>data-time</strong> attribute specify the time of the animation in miliseconds. The second attribute specify the time of delay for animation of the specific element (of course in the miliseconds).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let\'s analyze the fragment of the code from the homepage animation:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;gkHeader&quot;&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;h1 data-start=&quot;{\'top\':\'-100px\', \'opacity\': 0, \'right\': \'30px\'}&quot; data-end=&quot;{\'top\': 45, \'opacity\': 1}&quot; data-delay=&quot;100&quot; data-time=&quot;500&quot;&gt;Welcome!&lt;/h1&gt;<br /><br />\r\n\r\n&lt;p data-start=&quot;{\'opacity\':0, \'top\': \'150px\', \'right\': \'30px\'}&quot; data-end=&quot;{\'opacity\': 1}&quot; data-delay=&quot;350&quot; data-time=&quot;350&quot;&gt;Sed ut perspiciat unde orodiaer leroacustiu mera reuentis mose keriasertas toresa.&lt;small&gt;Architecto beatae naseaeraciat kuiase undeosler miase osac usa ntiume uedearsteked icexplicabo nemo enim ipsam lertasevol uptatemia voluptas sit.&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;<br /><br />\r\n\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;gkHeaderHat&quot; data-start=&quot;{\'left\':\'40px\', \'opacity\': 0, \'top\': \'600px\'}&quot; data-end=&quot;{\'opacity\': 1, \'top\': 40}&quot; data-delay=&quot;0&quot; data-time=&quot;600&quot;&gt;Hat&lt;/div&gt;<br /><br />\r\n\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;gkHeaderOrder&quot; data-start=&quot;{\'bottom\':\'0px\', \'opacity\': 0, left: \'-300px\'}&quot; data-end=&quot;{\'opacity\': 1, \'left\': 30}&quot; data-delay=&quot;700&quot; data-time=&quot;250&quot;&gt;Order online&lt;/div&gt;<br /><br />\r\n\r\n&lt;div class=&quot;gkHeaderSign&quot; data-start=&quot;{\'bottom\':\'40px\', \'opacity\': 0, right: \'-300px\'}&quot; data-end=&quot;{\'opacity\': 1, \'right\': 40}&quot; data-delay=&quot;700&quot; data-time=&quot;250&quot;&gt;Chef Jeferson&lt;/div&gt;<br /><br />\r\n\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>As you can see the the <strong>h1</strong> element will animate <strong>top</strong> and <strong>opacity</strong> properties in <strong>500ms</strong> and will start after <strong>100ms</strong>. The paragraph will animate only <strong>opacity</strong> property in <strong>350ms</strong> and will start after <strong>350ms</strong> etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The very important is fact that the content of the <strong>data-start</strong> attribute specify the start position of the animated element and all elements are positioned absolutely.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\";s:4:\"body\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"catid\";s:1:\"7\";s:10:\"created_by\";s:2:\"42\";s:16:\"created_by_alias\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"modified\";s:19:\"2012-04-29 14:03:19\";s:11:\"modified_by\";s:2:\"42\";s:6:\"params\";O:9:\"JRegistry\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";O:8:\"stdClass\":67:{s:14:\"article_layout\";s:9:\"_:default\";s:10:\"show_title\";s:1:\"1\";s:11:\"link_titles\";s:1:\"0\";s:10:\"show_intro\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"show_category\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"link_category\";s:1:\"0\";s:20:\"show_parent_category\";s:1:\"0\";s:20:\"link_parent_category\";s:1:\"0\";s:11:\"show_author\";s:1:\"0\";s:11:\"link_author\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"show_create_date\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"show_modify_date\";s:1:\"0\";s:17:\"show_publish_date\";s:1:\"0\";s:20:\"show_item_navigation\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"show_vote\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"show_readmore\";s:1:\"1\";s:19:\"show_readmore_title\";s:1:\"1\";s:14:\"readmore_limit\";s:3:\"100\";s:10:\"show_icons\";s:1:\"1\";s:15:\"show_print_icon\";s:1:\"0\";s:15:\"show_email_icon\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"show_hits\";s:1:\"0\";s:11:\"show_noauth\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"urls_position\";s:1:\"1\";s:23:\"show_publishing_options\";s:1:\"1\";s:20:\"show_article_options\";s:1:\"1\";s:25:\"show_urls_images_frontend\";s:1:\"1\";s:2